Z||000016||Reptyx||01-07-2001||04:17 PM||reptyx@hotmail.com|| <IMG SRC="http://www.ettnet.se/~egils/dolphin_reptyx_h.jpg"> <p>Okay, here goes! ^_^<p>The flying turtles: you just push a turtle straight up through the surface, and it'll hover there, happily floating in thin air, like some Great A'Tuin wannabe.<p>The bug I've suffered worst from is connected to the Great White on level 2. If you lurk inside a hole, eventually it will push itself into the hole and get stuck, but the only things you find in its mouth are as usual just a lot of teeth and a quick way to become shark chow. It looks pretty buggy when it flails right through the solid rock, but I thought, what the hey, perhaps they couldn't do it better than that, so I kept on trying for a couple of weeks before I got it right.<p>The game has hanged a few times, sometimes so bad you have to restart the Dreamcast. Sometimes Ecco freezes while the rest of the game continues, so you have to wait until you run out of air.<p>Ending up on the wrong side of the walls has happened to me too, of course. The first time was on Roaring Forces when I was in fish shape so I couldn't just wait and die, I had to restart the level.<p>Some small things, like baby turtles and transculent jellyfish, swing around when you turn, so it's hard to shake them out of your field of vision.<p>Sometimes the music stops and all you hear is a faint weird noise.<p>If you try to tail-walk in the pools of Hanging Waters, you'll get a splashing noisy camera-shaking chaos. (I thought dolphins were supposed to elegantly cut through the water surface, not bounce off it! o_O)<p>That's all I can think of for now. I really think they should've done some more testing before they released it, they shouldn't have given my Ecco-hating brother an opportunity to point out how buggy it is... ^^;<br>
