Z||000019||Histronic||01-07-2001||08:32 PM||john__cool@hotmail.com||<IMG SRC="http://histronic.tripod.com/signiturelizard.gif">I tried that eel thingy.  After the cut scene took me back to the main pool, I went through the place again.  There was no music or eel chasing me.  I could turn around and explore the whole tunnel - I had 360 degree movement.  I swam right up to the harmless eels.  I came to the conclusion that the first one (farthest from the rocks) is the one that chases you, for some reason now harmless.  The second eel is the one that gets a face full of avalanche.  (You can clip through them and such, meaning that there is still some research to be done on the subject.)  The change in camera when Ecco avoids the avalanche disguises this.  By the way, using two identical objects for different purposes is more popular than you think, as it has been demonstrated in Sonic and Knuckles.  If you put this on your Interesting things page, Blackie, remember you heard it here first.
